<div class="lang-en">
<section id="overview">
  <h2>What Is a BaZi Chart?</h2>
  <p>BaZi (<span class="chinese-char">八字</span>, Bāzì) translates literally as "eight characters." It is the classical Chinese system of analysing a person's birth moment using four pairs of <a href="/heavenly-stems-earthly-branches/">Heavenly Stems and Earthly Branches</a> &mdash; one pair for the year, month, day, and hour of birth. Each pair is called a <strong>pillar</strong> (<span class="chinese-char">柱</span>), hence the English name "Four Pillars of Destiny."</p>
  <p>A BaZi chart is not a horoscope. It does not predict events with fixed certainty. Instead, it maps your <strong>elemental composition at birth</strong> &mdash; the specific mix of Wood, Fire, Earth, Metal, and Water that defines your innate tendencies, strengths, challenges, and how you interact with the changing elements of time.</p>
  <p>To follow this guide, you will need your BaZi chart. Use our <a href="/bazi-calculator/">BaZi Calculator</a> to generate one from your birth date, time, and location.</p>
</section>
</div>
<div class="lang-tc">
<section id="overview">
  <h2>什麼是八字命盤？</h2>
  <p>八字（<span class="chinese-char">八字</span>，Bāzì）字面意思為「八個字」。這是中國傳統命理體系，通過出生年、月、日、時四組<a href="/heavenly-stems-earthly-branches/">天干地支</a>來分析一個人的出生時刻。每組稱為一<strong>柱</strong>（<span class="chinese-char">柱</span>），因此又稱「四柱推命」。</p>
  <p>八字命盤並非占星術。它不會以絕對的確定性預測事件。相反，它描繪你<strong>出生時的五行組合</strong>——木、火、土、金、水的特定配比，定義了你的天性傾向、優勢、挑戰，以及你如何與時間流轉中的五行變化互動。</p>
