<div class="lang-en">
<section id="day-master">
  <h2>Your Day Master (<span class="chinese-char">日主</span>)</h2>
  <p>The Heavenly Stem of your day pillar is your <strong>Day Master</strong> (Rì Zhǔ, <span class="chinese-char">日主</span>). It is the single most important character in your chart &mdash; your elemental identity. Everything else in the chart is interpreted <em>in relation to</em> the Day Master.</p>
  <p>There are ten possible Day Masters, corresponding to the ten Heavenly Stems:</p>
  <table class="elements-table">
    <thead><tr><th>Day Master</th><th>Element</th><th>Metaphor</th><th>Core Quality</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td>Jiǎ (<span class="chinese-char">甲</span>)</td><td>Yang Wood</td><td>Great tree</td><td>Principled, upright, stubborn</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Yǐ (<span class="chinese-char">乙</span>)</td><td>Yin Wood</td><td>Vine, flower</td><td>Flexible, adaptive, tenacious</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Bǐng (<span class="chinese-char">丙</span>)</td><td>Yang Fire</td><td>The sun</td><td>Radiant, generous, expansive</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Dīng (<span class="chinese-char">丁</span>)</td><td>Yin Fire</td><td>Candle flame</td><td>Focused, warm, perceptive</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Wù (<span class="chinese-char">戊</span>)</td><td>Yang Earth</td><td>Mountain</td><td>Solid, reliable, immovable</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Jǐ (<span class="chinese-char">己</span>)</td><td>Yin Earth</td><td>Garden soil</td><td>Nurturing, detail-oriented, receptive</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Gēng (<span class="chinese-char">庚</span>)</td><td>Yang Metal</td><td>Sword, axe</td><td>Decisive, brave, sharp</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Xīn (<span class="chinese-char">辛</span>)</td><td>Yin Metal</td><td>Jewellery, needle</td><td>Refined, precise, sensitive</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Rén (<span class="chinese-char">壬</span>)</td><td>Yang Water</td><td>Ocean, river</td><td>Powerful, restless, ambitious</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Guǐ (<span class="chinese-char">癸</span>)</td><td>Yin Water</td><td>Rain, dew</td><td>Intuitive, gentle, deep</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
  <p>Identifying your Day Master is the first step in any BaZi reading. It answers the question: <em>"What element am I?"</em></p>
</section>
</div>
<div class="lang-tc">
